17 [10–406.
18 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
19 (2) “Assessment” means a charge imposed by a local jurisdiction on each
20 transportation network service that includes a passenger trip during transportation
21 network coverage period three as described in § 10–101(n)(1)(iii) of this title.
22 (3) “Exempt jurisdiction” means a county or municipal corporation that
23 imposed a tax, fee, or charge on for–hire transportation services provided on a per ride or
24 per passenger basis in that county or municipal corporation on or before January 1, 2015.
25 (b) (1) Except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection, this section does
26 not limit the authority of an exempt jurisdiction to impose an assessment, a tax, a fee, or a
27 charge on for–hire transportation services, including transportation network services.
28 (2) An exempt jurisdiction may not impose more than one assessment or
29 similar charge on a transportation network service.
30 (c) (1) In accordance with subsections (d) and (e) of this section, a county or
31 municipal corporation may impose an assessment under this section.

4 HOUSE BILL 1622
1 (2) Except in an exempt jurisdiction, an assessment by a county or
2 municipal corporation authorized by this section may not exceed 25 cents per trip.
3 (3) (i) Except as provided in subsection (e)(5) of this section, an
4 assessment may not be imposed on a transportation network service by both a county and
5 a municipal corporation.
6 (ii) If both a county and a municipal corporation impose an
7 assessment on a transportation network service in accordance with subsection (e)(5) of this
8 section, the sum of the assessments imposed by both jurisdictions may not exceed 25 cents
9 per trip.
10 (4) The revenue generated from an assessment authorized under this
11 section shall be used for transportation purposes.
12 (d) (1) This subsection applies to a county or municipal corporation that
13 licensed or regulated taxicab services on or before January 1, 2015, either directly or
14 through the Commission as provided in § 10–202 of this title.
15 (2) (i) A county, in accordance with subparagraph (ii) of this paragraph,
16 or a municipal corporation may impose an assessment on trips that originate in the county
17 or municipal corporation.
18 (ii) A county authorized to impose an assessment under this
19 subsection:
20 1. may impose an assessment on trips that originate in any
21 area of the county; but
22 2. may not impose an assessment in a municipal corporation
23 that is authorized to impose an assessment under this subsection.
24 (3) If a county or municipal corporation authorized to impose an
25 assessment under this subsection has not authorized an assessment on trips that originate
26 in the county or municipal corporation by July 1, 2016, the county or municipal corporation
27 is subject to subsection (e) of this section.
28 (4) (i) If a county authorized to impose an assessment under this
29 subsection plans to impose an assessment under this section, the county shall notify the
30 municipal corporations in the county of the county’s intent to impose an assessment.
31 (ii) If a municipal corporation authorized to impose an assessment
32 under this subsection plans to impose an assessment under this section, the municipal
33 corporation shall notify the county of the municipal corporation’s intent to impose an
34 assessment.

