15 (6) (i) 1. The Comptroller may review or inspect each year, at a
16 transportation network company’s place of business or a mutually agreed location, records
17 necessary to ensure that the transportation network company has remitted to the
18 Comptroller the correct revenues and allocations.
19 2. Nothing in this subparagraph is intended to limit the
20 period covered by the Comptroller’s review or inspection, which may include more than 1
21 year.
22 (ii) Records or information provided to the Comptroller by a
