22 (a) In its operation of an airport, airport facility, or air navigation facility owned
23 or controlled by this State, the Administration, with the approval of the Secretary and
24 subject to the direction of the Commission, may contract, lease, or otherwise arrange with
25 any person to:
26 (1) Provide the person with services furnished by the Administration or its
27 agents at the airport or facility; or
28 (2) Grant to the person the privilege of:
29 (i) Using or improving for commercial purposes any part of the
30 airport or facility; or
31 (ii) Supplying services, facilities, goods, commodities, or other things
32 at the airport or facility.

12 HOUSE BILL 1622
1 (b) (1) (I) For the privileges granted, the Administration may establish,
2 SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, any terms and conditions and
3 fix any charges, rentals, or fees that:
4 [(i)] 1. Are reasonable and uniform for the same class of privilege
5 or service;
6 [(ii)] 2. Are established with due regard to the property and
7 improvements used and the expenses of operation to this State; and
8 [(iii)] 3. Do not deprive the public of its rightful, equal, and
9 uniform use of any part of the airport or facility.
10 (II) THE ADMINISTRATION MAY NOT FIX ANY CHARGES,
11 RENTALS, OR FEES ON THE PRIVILEGE OF PROVIDING TRANSPORTATION NETWORK
12 SERVICES, AS DEFINED IN § 10–101 OF THE PUBLIC UTILITIES ARTICLE, AT THE
13 AIRPORT OR FACILITY.
14 (2) The Administration shall monitor the charges, fees, or prices of any
15 goods or services offered to the public by persons granted the privilege under this section.
16 Every contract, lease, or other arrangement shall provide that charges, fees, or prices:
17 (i) May not be increased without the prior approval of the
18 Administration; and
19 (ii) Are to be reasonable. In determining reasonableness the
20 Administration shall consider the charges, fees, or prices for the same goods or services at
21 comparable airports.
22 (3) The Administration shall:
23 (i) Monitor the employment practices under Title 20, Subtitle 6 of
24 the State Government Article of persons granted privileges under this section; and
25 (ii) Refer for investigation all alleged violations of § 20–606 of the
26 State Government Article to the Commission on Civil Rights, the Equal Employment
27 Opportunity Commission, or any appropriate State or federal administrative body.
28 (c) (1) In this subsection, “commercial activity” means the sale,
29 merchandising, marketing, or promotion of any goods or services.
30 (2) Commercial activity is permitted at an airport operated by the
31 Administration only when expressly authorized by and in a manner prescribed by the
32 Administration.

